HOUSE RESOLUTION 105
By Zachary
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Donald Dodgen on his
induction into the TSSAA Hall of Fame.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this legislative body should specially
recognize those individuals who have performed their duties with uncommon devotion and
enthusiasm and who, through their magnificent exploits, have brought honor to this State; and
WHEREAS, Donald Dodgen, the current athletic director at Farragut High School, is one
such individual, whose nearly sixty years of excellence as a player, coach, and administrator
have made him a towering figure in Tennessee high school sports; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Dodgen was inducted into the Tennessee Secondary School Athletic
Association (TSSAA) Hall of Fame on April 7, 2025, an honor reserved for those who have
demonstrated exceptional dedication, leadership, and impact in the field of Tennessee high
school athletics; and
WHEREAS, Donald Dodgen's remarkable journey began as a basketball standout and
High School All-American at Gatlinburg-Pittman High School (Class of 1969), and he continued
to shine as a collegiate athlete at Tennessee Wesleyan College, earning eventual induction into
the school's Hall of Fame as both a player and a coach; and
WHEREAS, over the course of his remarkable thirty-eight-year coaching career, Mr.
Dodgen served at McMinn County High School, Gatlinburg-Pittman High School, and ultimately
Farragut High School in 1996 and left an unforgettable impact on each school that he served;
and
WHEREAS, as a basketball coach, Donald Dodgen achieved an overall record of 655
wins and 309 losses, which speaks to his consistency and excellence in a career that included a
trip to the state tournament in 1982 and multiple region and district championships; and
