WHEREAS, Donald Dodgen has been duly recognized for his athletic expertise through
induction into numerous halls of fame, including the Tennessee Wesleyan Hall of Fame,
Gatlinburg-Pittman High School Hall of Fame, Farragut High School Hall of Fame, and the KIL
Coaches Association Hall of Fame; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Dodgen's positive impact on the lives of students, athletes, coaches,
and administrators will continue to resound for many years to come, and it is appropriate that we
acknowledge his contributions to high school athletics in Tennessee; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, that we honor and
congratulate Donald Dodgen upon his induction into the TSSAA Hall of Fame, where he will be
immortalized alongside his peers in the annals of Tennessee athletic history.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy.
